overview: From 2025-10-23 to 2025-10-24, ethereum-optimism/optimism had 14 new PRs (14 merged), 0 new issues, and 33 active contributors.

topIssues.title: Forwards-comaptible gameType retrieval in OPCM
topIssues.author: Inphi
topIssues.body:
As a follow-up to [#17832](https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/pull/17832), we should update all OPCM functions that read the game type from dispute game implementations to use the new creator pattern.

The game type is no longer stored as an attribute of the dispute game implementation. This isnâ€™t an issue, since we always know the game type based on the key used to locate it from the factory.

This isn't a requirement for the creator pattern feature. We will need it for the next upgrade after the creator pattern.

topIssues.title: Update OPCMStandardValidator to handle new dispute game contracts
topIssues.author: mbaxter
topIssues.body:
## Description

The `OPContractsManagerStandardValidator` currently pulls a lot of data from the dispute game implementations set in the `DisputeGameFactory`.  For version 2 of these contracts, some of this data is no longer accessible on the implementation.  We'll need to find a way to continue validating the dispute game config.  We should be able to just inspect the `DisputeGameFactory.gameArgs` data to validate the parameters that are no longer stored on the implementation.

topIssues.title: Jovian: Only deposit transactions in activation block
topIssues.author: sebastianst
topIssues.body:
Like in Interop, the Jovian activation block must only contain deposit transactions.

This rule has recently been added to the specs (https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/specs/pull/791). It still needs to be enforced in the Go and Rust implementations.
- sequencer needs to set `noTxPool` to `true`
- derivation batch verification needs to drop non-empty activation batch

topIssues.title: [DA Footprint Limit] Investigate why block right after genesis still has 0 gas scalar
topIssues.author: sebastianst
topIssues.body: In current tests, block 1 after genesis still has a 0 gas scalar. But it should have the default scalar already. Current tests skip the first block because of this.

topPRs.title: opcm-standard-validator: Re-enable tests for v2 contracts, validate proposer
topPRs.author: mbaxter
topPRs.body:
<!--
Contributions welcome! See https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/.github/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md
-->

**Description**
This PR updates `OPContractsManagerStandardValidator` (StandardValidator) to include validation for the `proposer` on `PermissionedDisputeGame`'s, and it re-enables and updates tests for the StandardValidator when the `DevFeatures.DEPLOY_V2_DISPUTE_GAMES` feature flag is enabled.

This PR builds on a few previous PRs:
-  #17782 - which is needed to set up tests correctly
-  #17874 - which introduced updates to `OPContractsManagerStandardValidator` to read some game parameters from the new `gameArgs` mapping in `DisputeGameFactory`.

**Tests**

Tests have been re-enabled and updated.

**Metadata**
Closes #17267

topPRs.title: op-node/rollup: Drop non-empty batches for Jovian activation block
topPRs.author: sebastianst
topPRs.body:
**Description**

Adds Jovian to the list of forks (before, only Interop) that forbids non-empty batches at the activation block. If the Jovian activation batch contains transactions, it is now dropped.

Also add and improve modular fork handling for the rollup config, which simplified writing the test and adds helpers to more easily write modular tests that work for all forks in the future.

**Tests**

Unit tests added for batch validity checks.

Action/proofs test added to assert that activation batcher with transactions are dropped.

**Additional context**

<!--
Add any other context about the problem you're solving.
-->

**Metadata**

Fixes https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/issues/17704

Interesting historical context, this has already been implemented once at https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/pull/14797
